  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Aide alimentaire au N&#xE9;pal - PAM 2008</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Aid in Nepal - WFP 2008</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite a ceasefire and Comprehensive Peace Agreement signed in 2006, there has been recent volatility in several regions of Nepal. This instability has hindered the population&apos;s access to basic services, including food. An estimated 42 out of 75 districts throughout the country are currently experiencing food shortages.   CIDA&apos;s contribution is used to help the World Food Programme provide emergency food assistance to conflict-affected populations. Special emphasis is given to targeting women, children, ethnic minorities and vulnerable indigenous groups. This operation is expected to meet the food aid needs of an estimated 1.3 million beneficiaries.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Malgr&#xE9; un cessez-le-feu et la signature en 2006 d&apos;un accord de paix global, certaines r&#xE9;gions du N&#xE9;pal ont connu r&#xE9;cemment des p&#xE9;riodes d&apos;instabilit&#xE9;. Cette instabilit&#xE9; a emp&#xEA;ch&#xE9; la population d&apos;acc&#xE9;der aux services de base, notamment &#xE0; la nourriture. Selon les estimations, 42 districts sur 75 dans le pays font actuellement &#xE9;tat de p&#xE9;nuries alimentaires.   La contribution de l&apos;ACDI sert &#xE0; appuyer les activit&#xE9;s du Programme alimentaire mondial (PAM) visant &#xE0; fournir de l&apos;aide alimentaire d&apos;urgence aux populations touch&#xE9;es par le conflit. Une attention particuli&#xE8;re est accord&#xE9;e aux femmes, aux enfants, aux minorit&#xE9;s ethniques et aux populations indig&#xE8;nes vuln&#xE9;rables. Ce projet devrait r&#xE9;pondre aux besoins en aide alimentaire d&apos;environ 1,3 million de b&#xE9;n&#xE9;ficiaires.</narrative>
  </description>
